               <p>JOSEPH BAKER. I am a <rs id="t18270913-359-viclabel1995" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-359-victim2592 t18270913-359-viclabel1995"></join>. On the 14th of August I was coming home from my club, to the Maze, in the Borough, where I lodge. I was going across <placeName id="t18270913-359-crimeloc1996">Newgate-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-359-crimeloc1996" type="placeName" value="Newgate-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-359-crimeloc1996" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-359-off1993 t18270913-359-crimeloc1996"></join>, about a quarter before one o'clock; John Woods, one of my club-mates, had gone with me as far as there, and then left me; when he was gone I sat down on some boards, and fell asleep; the prisoner came and sat by me, and took my property; my jacket and side pockets were buttoned up- he awoke me, by untying my apron, and getting his hand into my pockets: he took out my purse and a bag, with my money in it. I had seen it all secure a quarter of an hour before. I was sober, but being tired I fell asleep.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Were you quite in your sober senses? A. Yes; I had only drank a little beer; this man came and sat down by me: I had dropped asleep, and was awoke by his fumbling about; he was about five minutes in doing it - I did not seize him, because it did not directly strike me that there was any thing wrong- it was not possible for me to drop these things from my pocket; I was not off my legs five minutes; the clock had struck one before I sat down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-359-person2593">
                  JOHN 
                  SPEECHLEY
               <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2593" type="surname" value="SPEECHLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2593" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2593" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The watchman brought the prisoner to me, and gave me this bag, containing a knife and some buttons - I found this tobacco-box on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-359-person2594">
                  SAMUEL 
                  BOND
               <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2594" type="surname" value="BOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2594" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-359-person2594" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the watchman. At half-past one o'clock the prosecutor called Stop thief! I saw the prisoner running and two men after him; I stopped him, and he gave me this bag and knife.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did not the prisoner tell you that what he had, he had picked up? A. Yes; the prisoner pulled the bag out of his pocket, and gave it me, and then the prosecutor gave charge of him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
